    <note>Yang(2) Bangai [13188] In Yang(2) Wanli's funerary inscription for his grandson-in-law, Liu(2) Datong [27294], Bangai is identified as Yang(2) Wanli's granduncle and Bangai's son #1, Zhenwen, as Wanli's uncle. Since Bangai's father, Tong [13187] and Wanli's great grandfather, Kai [15897], were different, Kan [10563] must be Bangai's grandfather and Wanli's great great grandfather, which would make Bangai's great grandfather, Heng [13186], the son of Lu [10562] and the father of Kan. Jiangxi TZ, 21.21a (juren in 1110), 39a; Yang Wanli, WJ, 118.21a-28a. CBD, 4, 3170-1.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1110:  Juren.</note>
